<refnamediv><refname>set-hadb-info</refname><refpurpose> sets the HADB database attributes</refpurpose></refnamediv>
<refsynopsisdiv><title>&synp-tt;</title>
<cmdsynopsis><command>set-hadb-info</command>&synopsis-common;
<arg>&Dash;&Dash;hosts <replaceable>hadb-host-list</replaceable></arg><arg choice="opt"> &Dash;&Dash;haagentport <replaceable>port_number</replaceable> </arg><arg choice="opt">&Dash;&Dash;haadminpassword <replaceable>password</replaceable></arg><arg choice="opt">&Dash;&Dash;haadminpasswordfile <replaceable>
file_name</replaceable></arg><arg choice="req"> <replaceable>cluster-name  (name=value)[:name-value]*</replaceable></arg>
</cmdsynopsis></refsynopsisdiv>
<refsect1><title>&desc-tt;</title>
<para>The <command>set-hadb-info</command> command sets the HADB database attributes, such as the list of nodes in the HADB domain, database runtime attributes, status of the database, etc. You can specify these attributes as name-value pairs for each cluster.</para>
<para>This command is supported in remote mode only.</para>
</refsect1>
<refsect1><title>&opts-tt;</title>
<para></para>
<variablelist termlength="medium">&options-common;
<varlistentry><term><option role="nodash"></option> <option role="nodash">&Dash;&Dash;hosts</option></term><listitem><para>A comma separated list of host names where the HADB instance is configured. The number of hosts must be greater than 1 and must be an even number. The same host names can be repeated.
Use fully qualified hostnames when specifying the hostlist interfaces explicitly for hosts with multiple network interfaces.</para>
</listitem></varlistentry>
<varlistentry><term><option role="nodash"></option> <option role="nodash">&Dash;&Dash;haagentport</option></term><listitem><para>Identifies the number of the HA agent port. The default is 1862.</para>
</listitem></varlistentry>
<varlistentry><term><option role="nodash"></option> <option role="nodash">&Dash;&Dash;haadminpassword</option></term><listitem><para>Identifies the HA administrator password.</para>
</listitem></varlistentry>
<varlistentry><term><option role="nodash"></option> <option role="nodash">&Dash;&Dash;haadminpasswordfile</option></term><listitem><para>The file containing the high-availability password associated with the administrative instance. The password is defined in the following form: HADBM_ADMINPASSWORD=<replaceable>
password</replaceable>, HADBM_DBPASSWORD=<replaceable>password</replaceable>, HADBM_SYSTEMPASSWORD=<replaceable>password</replaceable>. Where <replaceable>password</replaceable> is the actual HA administrator password for the domain.</para>
</listitem></varlistentry>
</variablelist></refsect1>
<refsect1><title>&oper-tt;</title>
<variablelist termlength="narrow">
<varlistentry><term><replaceable>cluster-name </replaceable></term><listitem><para>Name of the HADB database. Specify the attributes and its values as a list of property name/value pairs, which are separated by a colon.</para>
</listitem></varlistentry>
</variablelist></refsect1>
